cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and the ability of recurrent neural networks to understand and produce new utterances. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it deals with the capabilities and limitations of neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it specifically focuses on recurrent neural networks, and cs.CV (Computer Vision) because the paper includes a proof-of-concept experiment in neural machine translation.
